# Node.js Development Guidelines

## Language & Framework
- Primary language: JavaScript/TypeScript
- Use Node.js LTS versions
- Prefer TypeScript for new projects
- Use modern ES6+ features

## Code Style
- Use ESLint for linting
- Use Prettier for code formatting
- Follow Node.js best practices
- Use async/await instead of callbacks
- Prefer const/let over var

## Testing
- Use Jest or Vitest for unit and integration tests
- Write tests for all new features
- Aim for high test coverage
- Use descriptive test names

## Package Management
- Use npm or yarn (specify which in project)
- Keep package.json dependencies up to date
- Use exact versions for production dependencies when appropriate
- Run security audits regularly

## Project Structure
- Follow Node.js project conventions
- Separate concerns (routes, controllers, services, models)
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Keep configuration files organized

## Docker & Deployment
- Use Docker for containerization
- Use Docker Compose for local development
- Optimize Docker images for production
- Use multi-stage builds when appropriate

## Code Quality
- Write clean, readable, maintainable code
- Add comments for complex logic
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Follow SOLID principles
- Keep functions small and focused

